What a delight and challenge to work on Sneed, our new Ferengi. Brought to life by @vincentvandykefx and team. The execution was flawless. These images represent the design model proposed. Attention was spent on honoring the canon and Vincent’s love of the character was my beacon. Thanks Vincent❤️ And thanks to @terrymatalas for all the input and guidance. Performed by @aaronastanford

More on Sneed, Picard’s new Ferengi. Adding character to a character is always fun. Coming up with backstory…prison tattoos, scars, battle damage, gold tooth. Always fun to imagine and execute, as best as I can with the tools I use, a design that communicates the intent. Done in ZBrush and then rendered in Keyshot. @vincentvandykefx knocked it out if the park. Application by @vincentvandykefx and @jrmackinnon and team. And thank you @terrymatalas for your guidance on this season! Performed by @aaronastanford @maxonzbrush @keyshot3d @startrekonpplus @startrekpicardofficial

Such a treat to get to participate in the world of 65 with @beckandwoods Amazing guys! A unique breed of writers and directors. Grateful for the opportunity and experience. This is a model of the emaciated T-Rex. Done in @maxonzbrush #65 @65movie

Picard, season 3, Borg Queen. Assimilation issues. Designed and sculpted in @maxonzbrush Big ol’ collaboration with @vincentvandykefx and @jrmackinnon Design NEVER starts without their input.
@startrek @startrekonpplus #borgqueen

Borg Queen lair. Picard, season 3 finale. These were early on in the process and clearly unused as time and budget were not in stride with the concept. And, to be fair, I was attempting to push the envelope a bit here, so I was not surprised that we couldn’t use them. Regardless, a fun exploration. The forms were inspired by the internal workings of the queens neural core in her crown from Season 2. Collaboration with @vincentvandykefx and @jrmackinnon Design NEVER starts without their input.
@startrek @startrekonpplus #borgqueen

The trouble with TRIBBLES? You never see their underbelly. Well, now you do….sorta. These were ideas for possible undersides of the Tribble anatomy. They need to move, eat, poop, mate, etc. It’s all there😉 Unused but fun to do. @startrekonpplus @startrek #tribble #tribbles
This little guy from 65. @65movie
More of this guy from @65movie
Early versions of the Rex from @65movie Emancipated and roughed in.

Check out this film!!! From @blumhouse Find the trailer and be awed by the performances!!! @kylegface consistently hits ‘em out of the park. You’re amazing, my friend!!! And the rest of the cast is incredible as well. Check out @johnnyberchtold , another super talent.

Going through some old boxes in the garage and found this very little guy. An early study from the @65movie . I used my @formlabs form2 printer for this to test out balance. I often do this on bipedal creatures to ensure that it can actual stand on its own. I was more shocked about the fact that his wee fingers were intact as it was floating around in a box with other stuff.

Last day to vote (I think). Such a privilege to be associated with these amazing artists and people. Best of luck to you all and the other nominees as well!
Much love❤️
Feeling all the love

A seasonal post I love to share. Parisian hot chocolate with fleur de sel. A delicious drink from the Angelina cafe in Paris. Made at home. Happy holidays. 6oz chopped bittersweet chocolate, 2 cups whole milk, 2 tablespoons light brown sugar. Warm milk in heavy pan, add chocolate and gently whisk until melted. If you want it thicker (this is the way to go) do a very very light boil for 2 to 3 minutes until desired thickness. Stirring constantly. Serve with a dash of sea salt. A little goes a long way as it’s rich.
Using the latest tech!!! #apple @apple

In the spirit of the season and Parisian chocolate and Wonka, here’s an upgraded version of my previous sipping chocolate post. Added fresh whipping cream and some magic sprinkles from an area near Hangdoodles.
Check out my bud @katezambrano and her new kit that just came out. She’s a force of talent and generosity with her skills! Give her a follow and see how she does her magic.
